message:
P3, I’ll play 5. You play 3. Here’s why:  
If P1 picks 5 he collides with me and you +3→7 to lead;  
if he picks 1 you +3→7 to lead;  
if he picks 3 he collides with you and I smash +5→10 and become the main threat.  
Either way, 3 is your only chance to not end up at ≤5. Picking 1 or 5 leaves you last. Lock in 3 and let’s go.
